A neat (though somewhat involved) way to solve this is to place all integers on a hex‐grid in “axial” coordinates and work out which hexagon corresponds to 2026, then find the coordinates of its six neighbors, and finally convert those neighbors back to their integer labels.  Here is a complete outline:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1.  The ring structure and where 2026 lies
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In a standard hex–spiral about 1, the “rings” around 1 have sizes:
 • Ring 0: just the center cell 1.
 • Ring k (for k ≥ 1) contains 6k numbers.

One can show that the last number on ring k is  
   3k(k+1) + 1.  
Hence ring k goes from  
   3(k−1)k + 2   up through   3k(k+1) + 1.

We want k so that 2026 lies in ring k.  By trial or by formula,

 • Ring 25 ends at 3·25·26 + 1 = 1951.
 • Ring 26 ends at 3·26·27 + 1 = 2107.

Since 1951 < 2026 ≤ 2107, the number 2026 is on ring 26.  The first number on ring 26 is 1952.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2.  Axial coordinates and labeling
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

A convenient way to label a hex‐grid is via “axial” coordinates (q,r).  One may place
  1  at  (0,0),
then ring k consists of all cells whose “hex distance” from (0,0) is exactly k (i.e.  
  max(|q|, |r|, |q+r|) = k  
in the usual cube‐coordinate interpretation).

Moreover, we enumerate ring k in counterclockwise order starting from the “easternmost” corner (k,0).  Concretely, for ring 26:  
 – corner 0 is (26, 0),  
 – corner 1 is (26, −26),  
 – corner 2 is (0, −26),  
 – corner 3 is (−26, 0),  
 – corner 4 is (−26, 26),  
 – corner 5 is (0, 26),  
and we traverse each of the six edges in 26 steps.

The integer labels on ring 26 run from 1952 up to 2107 (inclusive).  So if one calls  
     ring26Coord(i)  
the axial coordinate of the ith cell around ring 26 (with i = 0..(6·26−1) = 155), then  
     1952 + i  
is the integer label of that cell.

Since 2026 is the (2026 − 1952) = 74th cell in ring 26 (index i = 74), we find its coordinates by figuring out which edge of the ring and how far along:

• Each side of ring 26 has length 26.  
• e = 74 // 26 = 2  tells us it is on “edge 2” of the ring,  
• s = 74 mod 26 = 22 means it is the 22nd step along that edge.

Corner 2 of ring 26 is (0, −26).  Edge 2 proceeds in direction (−1,+1) each step.  Hence

   ring26Coord(74) 
   = corner2 + 22⋅(−1,+1) 
   = (0, −26) + (−22, +22) 
   = (−22, −4).

Therefore, in axial coordinates, 2026 sits at (q,r) = (−22, −4).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.  Finding the six neighbors of (−22, −4)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In axial coordinates (q,r), the six neighbors are given by adding each of the “unit” hex‐directions:

  (q+1, r), (q+1, r−1), (q, r−1),  
  (q−1, r), (q−1, r+1), (q, r+1).

Hence from (−22, −4) the six neighbors are:

 1) (−21, −4)
 2) (−21, −5)
 3) (−22, −5)
 4) (−23, −4)
 5) (−23, −3)
 6) (−22, −3).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4.  Converting each neighbor back to its integer label
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Each neighbor (q,r) lies on some ring k′ = max(|q|, |r|, |q+r|).  
Then one finds which index i it has around ring k′ in the same counterclockwise labeling, and hence its integer label is  
   ringStart(k′) + i  
where ringStart(k′) = 3(k′−1)k′ + 2 is the first label on ring k′.

Below is the summary of each neighbor’s ring and label:

 • N1 = (−21, −4).  
   k′ = max(21, 4, |−25|) = 25.  
   One finds i = 71 on ring 25, so label = 1802 + 71 = 1873.  

 • N2 = (−21, −5).  
   k′ = max(21, 5, 26) = 26.  
   i = 73 on ring 26, so label = 1952 + 73 = 2025.  

 • N3 = (−22, −5).  
   k′ = 27.  
   i = 76 on ring 27, so label = 2108 + 76 = 2184.  

 • N4 = (−23, −4).  
   k′ = 27.  
   i = 77 on ring 27, so label = 2108 + 77 = 2185.  

 • N5 = (−23, −3).  
   k′ = 26.  
   i = 75 on ring 26, so label = 1952 + 75 = 2027.  

 • N6 = (−22, −3).  
   k′ = 25.  
   i = 72 on ring 25, so label = 1802 + 72 = 1874.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
5.  Summing these six labels
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The six neighbors’ labels are

  1873, 2025, 2184, 2185, 2027, 1874.

Their total is

  1873 + 2025 + 2184 + 2185 + 2027 + 1874 = 12168.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Answer
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The sum of the six neighbors of 2026 in that hexagonal spiral is 12168.
